-- Tepco Restarts Anegasaki No. 3 Thermal Unit, Rim Says
-- B y   G e a r o i d   R e i d y
-- 2012-07-23T05:22:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-23/tepco-restarts-anegasaki-no-3-thermal-unit-rim-says-correct-.html
(Corrects month of restart in first paragraph.)  Tokyo  Electric Power Co. restarted
the No. 3 gas-fired unit at its Anegasaki power plant in Chiba
prefecture, near Tokyo, on July 21 following repairs after a
steam leak, Rim Intelligence reported on its website.  The utility halted the 600-megawatt unit on June 23.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gearoid Reidy in Tokyo at 
